%h2
  Registration

  %p
    The ANRW 2019 will be held at the
    %a{ :href => "https://www.ietf.org/how/meetings/105/hotel/" } Fairmont The Queen Elizabeth Hotel
    in Montreal, Quebec, Canada, on Monday 22 July 2019. The workship is
    co-located with the
    %a{ :href => "https://www.ietf.org/how/meetings/105/" } IETF 105 meeting
    which runs from 20-26 July in the same venue.

  %p
    All attendees
    %b must
    register for the ANRW. Registration provides for admittance to the ANRW
    on Monday 22 July 2019, and to the IETF welcome reception and tutorials
    on Sunday 21 July 2019.

  %p
    Registration for in-person attendance at the ANRW costs $150 USD for
    all attendees that are
    %b not
    also attending the IETF 105 meeting. 
    Registration for the ANRW is free of charge for those
    who have registered for in-person attendance at
    %a{ :href => "https://www.ietf.org/how/meetings/105/" } IETF 105
    for the full week, on a day pass for Monday, or as a full-time student.
    The IETF registration fee is $150 USD for full-time students, and covers
    attendance at all IETF working groups, tutorials, and other sessions for
    the entire week, as well as the ANRW. 

  %p
    %a.btn.btn-primary{ :href => "https://www.ietf.org/how/meetings/register/", :role => "button" } Register for IETF 105 (optional)

  %p
    %a.btn.btn-primary{ :href => "https://anrw-reg.irtf.org/anrw-reg-2019.html", :role => "button" } Register for ANRW 2019

  %p
    You
    %b
      do not
    need to register for IETF 105 in order to attend ANRW. If you do want
    to attend both IETF and ANRW, remember to come back here and register
    for ANRW after completing your IETF registration.

  %p
    At least one author of each accepted paper
    %b
      must
    register for the ANRW, and attend in-person to present their paper.

  %p
    The ANRW will be streamed live and recorded. Remote participation will
    be provided using the IETF remote participation system. You can find
    more details and information on how to register for remote participation
    on the 
    %a{ :href => "https://www.ietf.org/how/meetings/105/" } IETF 105 meeting page.
    There is no charge for remote participation, but pre-registration is required.








